   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON EIGHT REGENERATION Scripture Reading: John 3:3-8, 36; 1:12-13; 1 Pet 1:3, 23; James 1:18; 1 Cor 4:15; 1 John 1:2; 2 Pet 1:4 OUTLINE The definition of regeneration John 1:13.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The way: To realize our need of the life of God John 3:3.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>To realize that our natural being needs to be buried in the water of baptism John 3:5.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To be born of the Spirit of God in our spirit John 3:5, 6b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>By believing into the Son of God John 3:36a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Through the Word of God in the gospel 1 Pet 1:23; James 1:18; 1 Cor 4:15.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The issue: Resurrected with Christ 1 Pet 1:3b; Eph 2:5a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Having the eternal and uncreated life 1 John 1:2.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Becoming a child of God John 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Partaking of the divine nature 2 Pet 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Born into the kingdom of God John 3:5.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Focus: To be regenerated is to have the life of God that we may be His children living in His kingdom according to the divine nature.</S>
   </TEXT>
